# Data Models & Storage

## Pet Entity

```typescript
{
  id: string
  name: string
  // source
  imageOriginalPath: string    // appData/pets/{id}/source/original.{ext}
  imageCompressedPath: string  // appData/pets/{id}/source/compressed.{ext}
  // generated
  imageMinimaxRawPath: string  // .../generated/minimax_raw.png
  imagePetPath: string         // .../generated/pet.png (transparent, desktop asset)
  styleType: PetStyleType      // MVP default 'petory'; later: pixel|sticker|plush|clay|cyber
  personality: string
  level: number
  exp: number
  createdAt: string
  updatedAt: string
  isActive: boolean
}
```

Legacy field `imageProcessedPath` → map to `imagePetPath` if encountered.

## UserSettings / InteractionLog / FocusSession

Unchanged — see AGENTS.md for fields and XP rules.

## Disk Layout

```
appData/pets/{petId}/source/original.{ext}
appData/pets/{petId}/source/compressed.{ext}
appData/pets/{petId}/generated/minimax_raw.png
appData/pets/{petId}/generated/pet.png
```

- DB stores paths only, never base64
- Regenerate overwrites `minimax_raw.png` and `pet.png`; keep or refresh `compressed` if re-uploaded

## Persistence Rules

- Single `isActive` pet in MVP
- Reserve `userId` null for future accounts
- Settings, window position, XP survive restart

## PetStyleType (reserve from MVP)

```typescript
type PetStyleType = 'petory' | 'pixel' | 'sticker' | 'plush' | 'clay' | 'cyber'
// MVP: always 'petory'; other values used when style picker ships
```

## Privacy APIs

Clear chat, delete pet folder, wipe all data, export JSON.
